Alembic environment for the games schema on the steam/games DB.

Scope: ONLY the `games` schema (models in reporting/gamesmodels.py).
The env's include_object filter keeps autogenerate blind to any other
schemas, and the alembic version table lives in the games schema
itself. Connection creds resolve via reporting.gamesdb.load_db_config:
a local config/steamdbconfig.json wins (dev), else the SecureString
SSM parameter /processor/config/steamdbconfig.json (prod — set the
secret once, every box with the task role can migrate); env.py refuses
to run when neither exists rather than falling back to dbconfig.json
(the reporting DB). The sqlalchemy.url in alembic.ini is a placeholder
that env.py overrides.

One-time prod setup (JSON shaped like dbconfig.json):

    aws ssm put-parameter --type SecureString \
        --name /processor/config/steamdbconfig.json \
        --value '{"USER":"...","PASS":"...","HOST":"...","PORT":"5432","DATABASE":"..."}'

plus ssm:GetParameter (+ kms:Decrypt) on that path for the task role.

Workflow (run from the processor repo root):

    # create/upgrade the schema
    alembic upgrade head

    # after changing reporting/gamesmodels.py
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"
    # review the generated file, then
    alembic upgrade head

Writers upsert by natural key (see reporting/gamesdb.py), so re-running
any ingest replaces its slice instead of duplicating it.
